Pre-Game Insights: The Blue Jays are looking to end a three-game road slide.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The teams square off Thursday for the sixth time this season. The Blue Jays lead the season series 3-2.
Marcus Semien has 26 doubles, two triples and 22 home runs while hitting.235 for the Rangers.
Vladimir Guerrero Jr. leads the Blue Jays with 71 extra base hits (42 doubles, a triple and 28 home runs).
Others: The Rangers are 38-69 in games when they have allowed at least one home run.
The Blue Jays have a 55-26 record in games when they record eight or more hits.
